   "body" : "By not having to lock `cs_main` every time we try to access block\r\ndata on disk, we can avoid slowing down concurrent tasks due to\r\nthreads waiting for the global lock to be released.\r\n\r\nAlso, solves a edge case race inside `ReadBlockFromDisk` where\r\nwe obtain the file position locking `cs_main` and then try to access\r\nthe file without it (the file could no longer exist if pruning occurred\r\njust in-between these two actions).\r\n\r\nContext from where this comes from #26966.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nI'm not totally happy with the shared_ptr usage for the local mutex\r\nbut it was needed to by-pass the `CBlockIndex` default copy\r\nconstructor existence (the mutex object has a deleted copy constructor).\r\n\r\nWill go deeper over removing the copy constructor in the coming days,\r\nso the shared_ptr can be erased too.",
